<h3>Well that should get you started</h3>

That should get you started in the wonderful world of Web Programming. I've given you the basics that will hopefully get you started in your early stages of learning. Don't worry if you don't get everything, this is just your introduction to it all. And don't be afraid to tell yourself that this industry/profession isn't right for you. Please don't give up just because it's hard or overwhelming, because it's hard for everyone. Watch the videos that I recommend more than once if you don't get it and by all means use Google if you don't understand a concept or run into any brick walls.";s:10:"post_title";s:42:"Getting Your Feet Wet with Web Development";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:32:"getting-feet-wet-web-development";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2014-01-05 23:17:51";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2014-01-05 23:17:51";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:29:"http://bryansiegel.com/?p=578";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:4:"post";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}}